# Code of Conduct

As contributors and maintainers of the CarbonKatha project, we pledge to foster an open and welcoming environment for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to creating a positive environment include:

- Being respectful and considerate of others' viewpoints and experiences.
- Using welcoming and inclusive language.
- Being empathetic towards other community members.
- Gracefully accepting constructive criticism and feedback.
- Focusing on the project's goals and the collective success of the community.

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, discrimination, or derogatory comments based on any personal characteristics mentioned above.
- Intimidation or threats, whether verbal or physical.
- Inappropriate or unwelcome advances, including unwanted attention or touching.
- Disruptive behavior that interferes with the project or community's functioning.
- Any form of trolling, spamming, or intentionally spreading misinformation.

## Responsibilities

Community members, including contributors, maintainers, and project leaders, have a responsibility to uphold these standards and create a safe and inclusive environment for everyone. This includes:

- Treating others with respect and kindness.
- Being mindful of how your words and actions may affect others.
- Taking responsibility for your behavior and the consequences of your actions.
- Refraining from engaging in behavior that violates this code of conduct.
- Reporting any instances of unacceptable behavior to the project maintainers.

## Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by contacting the project maintainers at projectcarbonkatha@gmail.com.. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly. The project maintainers are obligated to maintain confidentiality regarding the reporter of an incident.

Community members who violate this code of conduct may face consequences, including but not limited to:

- Temporary or permanent expulsion from the project's community spaces.
- Loss of privileges, such as the ability to contribute to the project or participate in community events.
- Other actions deemed appropriate by the project maintainers to address and rectify the situation.

We ask all community members to assist in ensuring the enforcement of this code of conduct by promptly reporting any instances of unacceptable behavior.
